OL,4,CTokyo Olympics: Composer Keigo Oyamada
OL,5,Cresigns over bullying at school
OL,6, A composer has quit the team creating
OL,7, the Tokyo Olympics opening ceremony
OL,8, after it emerged he had bullied
OL,9, classmates with disabilities at school.
OL,11,FOld magazine articles resurfaced in
OL,12,Fwhich Keigo Oyamada, 52, boasted of the
OL,13,Fbullying and said he had no regrets.
OL,15,FAfter the scandal broke, the performer
OL,16,Fapologised. But the outrage in Japan
OL,17,Fhas now led to his resignation.
OL,19,FIt is the latest setback for the games,
OL,20,Fwhich are opening on Friday under the
OL,21,Fshadow of the coronavirus outbreak.
